radiographic_examinations.findings: lesion with a low level of attenuation in the left kidney and some fluid and inflammation around the repaired abdominal aortic aneurysm; thickening of the distal bowel was noted.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Radiologists reported no clinically significant collection of fluid at the site of aneurysm repair; renal lesion was thought to be most likely a cyst.
